						<div class="postbody">Hello everyone, <br /><br />Firstable, sorry for my english, i'm french, <br /><br />So, this week end i tried to convert a JAP RockMan X3 to a Megaman X2...<br /><br />But it failed...<br /><br />How i proceeded :<br /><br />-Downloaded a Rom U of Megaman X2 (16Mb).<br />-Checked Header presence =&gt; Ok.<br />-Removed Protection with ucon64 =&gt; Ok.<br />-Burn the rom in a 27C160 with my GQ4X =&gt; Ok no error.<br />-And then soldered a socket following a GSU2 pinout on my Rockman X3 PCB.<br /><br />But, the problem is here : <br /><br />My game is booting, i can see the three blue lines intro... then Capcom Logo... And then i've got blackscreen. I can not access to the title screen...<br /><br />So i tried with a Megaman X3 Rom in a c160, putted in my socket, and it worked !<br /><br />But why isn't it working with Megaman X2?<br /><br />Can someome help me ? have you ever tried this mod ? Is this a pinout problem with this X2? a Rom problem (Tried with U and E Rom, same thing...).<br /><br />Thanks in advance,<br /><br />Br,<br /><br />Bool.</div>

