				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">RMX2/MMX2 uses 2x8Mbit ROM chips, RMX3/MMX3 uses 1x16Mbit ROM.  Here's what byuu told me about running RMX2 on an RMX3 board<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">And by the way, if you do attempt to flash in RMX2, it will need one tiny code patch. Somewhere in the game it writes #$01 to $7f52. That needs to be commented out or set to #$00. (I may have the bit flipped in my head again.) The register toggles whether banks 20-3f go to the second ROM chip or not. Which obviously there will only be one.</div></div>

					
							<br /><br />
